    <description>&brandShortName; tip of the day Archive</description>
    <language>en-us</language>
  
    <item>
      <title>…you can resize table with the mouse?</title>
      <description>Just show the rulers using View > Show/Hide > Rulers and
                   place the caret inside a table cell to see resizers appear.
      </description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can very easily customize a toolbar?</title>
      <description>Just right-click on it…</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you have direct access to the &brandShortName; community?</title>
      <description>Just select the Help menu.</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…&brandShortName; is cross-platform?</title>
      <description>&brandShortName; exists on a wide variety of operating systems, including
                   Windows, Mac OS X, many flavors of Linux, OS/2, …</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can create a new tab with a key combination?</title>
      <description>Control+n (Command+n on Mac OS X) will create a new blank tab</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can close the current tab with one key?</title>
      <description>Control-w (Command-w on Mac OS X) will close the current tab.</description>
    </item>

  </channel>
</rss>

